Also, I talked a lot about the meaning of life with my high-powered mother when she was in her finals months, dying of cancer, which led me to reevaluate many things in my own life. Her main regret was caring too much about her career and spending too much time and effort on the pursuit of power and money. So I abandoned my pursuit of higher positions on the research track and settled for a low-key teaching position. Basically I'm out of the academic rat race, and I'm feeling great (easy for me to do and say though, with my privileged background... Most of my colleagues can't afford to be as chill about any of this).

